&ldquo;Explore the ruined Imperial City of Metbetoch in search of lost secrets, powerful spells, and artifacts before your opponents can beat you to it!&rdquo;

Thematic scenario-based hexploration and area control game with quests and combat, where each player manages their party of adventurers improving skills, getting gear, and discovering secrets while fighting some of the most dangerous denizens that have infested the city's ruins and catacombs.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Paris Match is a weekly magazine, the French equivalent of the American magazine "Life". The &ldquo;Special Edition&rdquo; game was designed by the editorial staff of &ldquo;Paris Match&rdquo;. The game mechanism is inspired by Trivial Pursuit. We move pawns on a board, we draw a card from the theme corresponding to the square, and we must answer the ten questions asked.
The six themes are:
Science, technology and health (green);
Fashion and Lifestyles (Turquoise);
Politics and political events (blue);
Culture and entertainment (purple);
Sports and adventures (red);
Miscellaneous news and love stories (yellow).
The period of events goes from 1949 until the end of the eighties.
Each time a player answers a question correctly, he earn a token in the color of the theme. On the other hand, if he is wrong, it is up to his neighbor on the left to answer, and so on until the list of ten questions on the card is exhausted. When a player manages to accumulate 10 tokens, he wins a crown of the same color, which he stacks on his pawn. The winner is the one who first get the six crowns.

Two different litters of kittens were born and are discovering the most comfortable way to take long naps, in a cattery specially prepared for them. Which litter of kittens will get the most comfortable nap first?

The Game in 3 Steps:

     Distribute the baskets throughout the cattery;
     On your turn, move one of the kittens from your litter to a new pen;
     Line up your kittens in the room, or accommodate them in the same type of basket so they can take a comfortable nap while you win the game!


&mdash;description from the designer

Duas ninhadas diferentes de gatinhos nasceram e est&atilde;o descobrindo a forma mais confort&aacute;vel de tirar longas sonecas, em um gatil especialmente preparado para eles. Qual ninhada de gatinhos ir&aacute; tirar a soneca mais confort&aacute;vel primeiro?

O Jogo em 3 Passos:

     Distribua os balaios pelo gatil;
     Em seu turno, mova um dos gatinhos de sua ninhada para um novo balaio;
     Alinhe seus gatinhos no aposento, ou acomode-os em um mesmo tipo de balaio para que eles tirem uma soneca confort&aacute;vel enquanto voc&ecirc; ganha a partida!


&mdash;description from the designer (Portuguese)

The Ravensburg National Library, located in the central ward of the ring-shaped satellite city of Rio Grande, is busier than ever. A few days ago, the mysterious government agency Drei Magier offered a huge reward for any information about the person responsible for the downfall of the legendary witch Wiese.

Broom World Academians is a competitive research game set in a unique magical world. Each player becomes a laboratory director and aims to gather collaborators faster than other players. Players can compete individually or as teams.&nbsp;

All players simultaneously choose one of the three types of actions and its target, and if the action is successful, the player gains knowledge resources. Collaborator cards obtained with knowledge resources provide victory points. Players earn additional victory points through special abilities and collecting pairs.

As part of the Mini Rogue Season Two (The Council) Campaign, this is a collection of exclusive cards release during the crowdfunding campaign.

The collection adds:
- the "Druidess," a new character who can shapeshift into a powerful bear;
- "The Corrupted," a new boss eager to devour you;
- Liege of Pestilence;
- Spiritual Tiara;
- The Astrologer; and
- The Cartography Room.

Plate It Up is a party game of culinary creativity for up to 6 players. Each player takes on the role of an up-and-coming chef in a one-of-a-kind cooking competition.&nbsp;

Inspired by a Scenario and Star Ingredient, chosen by the Head Chef. All players, Head Chef Included, secretly craft their own unique dish using a random assortment of ingredients and compete for culinary supremacy!

With over 350 scenarios and ingredients, Plate It Up is stocked with endless fun to be had again and again!&nbsp;

&mdash;description from the publisher

This miniatures set is part of the Nuka Worlds wave for Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;Don&rsquo;t like Eyebots, always get the feeling that someone&rsquo;s watching me.&rsquo;
Eyebots. Are. Everywhere. A fact no less true in Nuka-World. Bobbing through the air blasting adverts and lasers in equal measure as they go. As prevalent across Nuka-World as everywhere else in the Wasteland, even more so in the Galactic Zone, Eyebots are the irritating, difficult to hit gift that keeps on giving.

This miniatures set is part of the Nuka Worlds wave for Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;Because clearly a Deathclaw wasn&rsquo;t bad enough!&rsquo;
When Old Dr McDermont had a cloning machine, he made a big mistake. By combining all the best aspects of the Jackson chameleon and the American alligator, he created one of the worst creatures to ever tear a Raider in half. Thankfully, he didn&rsquo;t live long enough to see his voraciously hungry children break out of their home and out into the big wide world, sadly, because they ate him. Circle of life, I suppose.

This miniatures set is compatible with both Fallout: Wasteland Warfare and Fallout: Factions, as part of the Nuka World wave for Wasteland Warfare and Season One of Factions..

&lsquo;Don&rsquo;t get caught? Does that matter if everyone knows you&rsquo;re just waiting for an excuse to kill them?&rsquo;
Fizztop Mountain may have once been a nice place to visit, once. Now it keeps its namesake alive by being packed to the brim with mountains of corpses. A lot like The Pack, most Disciples would describe their perfect Sunday as one full of blood and murder, though they tend to try and at least pretend they&rsquo;re not thinking about flaying the skin off everyone they meet most of the time. Fans of quick and efficient kills, the Disciples are thrill killers extraordinaire, always eager to move on to their next &lsquo;project&rsquo;.

This miniatures set is compatible with both Fallout: Wasteland Warfare and Fallout: Factions, as part of the Nuka World wave for Wasteland Warfare and Season One of Factions.

&lsquo;They say money makes the world go round, with the way Operators make money, it&rsquo;s going to be an empty world.&rsquo;
Without wanting to give them any props, the Operators are a well organised group, more like a crime syndicate than a raider gang. They follow orders, take on jobs, make their own gear and most of all, remain professional. Well armed and armored, Operators don&rsquo;t kill for fun (unlike the other gangs of Nuka-World), they kill for profit, or out of annoyance, which is occasionally fun. I guess they also kill for fun.

This miniatures set is compatible with both Fallout: Wasteland Warfare and Fallout: Factions, as part of the Nuka World wave for Wasteland Warfare and Season One of Factions.

&lsquo;The Pack are a lot like eating centuries old candy, bright, exciting and probably going to kill you.&rsquo;
Brightly coloured, bedecked in whatever interesting knick-knacks they can tape to themselves and wholly ruled by their moment to moment instincts, The Pack are less of a gang and more of&hellip; well, a pack. Following their Alpha to the end, members of The Pack tend to be spurred on to random acts of violence throughout the day, not too worried about the reason why, just if it&rsquo;ll be fun or not. Every choice they make tends to follow that logic, fun over all other things, sadly for everyone else, they think fighting is really, really fun.

This miniatures set is part of the Nuka Worlds wave for Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;Weaponizing Nuka-Cola is a sin, godless robots! How dare you waste what I could drink!&rsquo;
In the lovely Starlight Theatre, you could have once sat down and enjoyed slow service, flat cola, and cold food. Despite the centuries, not a lot has changed, bar the chances of death due to highly pressurised Nuka-Cola being fired through your skull - that&rsquo;s increased by about 5%. Manned by all forms of Robotic help, Nukatrons and Mr Frothys of all varieties can be found still serving the various corpses that act as the theatre&rsquo;s only guests for the last 100 years.

This miniatures set is part of the Nuka Worlds wave for Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;I don&rsquo;t care how dumb it looks, my caps are always on the Sentry bot.&rsquo;
The Model X9000 was meant to demonstrate the next wave of Robotic warfare, a sleek, child friendly model that was meant to draw the eye and then reduce all hostiles within a 1 mile radius to glowing radioactive ashes. The models on display at Nuka World were meant to act as an attraction for the public, but it&rsquo;s not overly common for attractions to be armed with gatling lasers, at least not to my knowledge.

This miniatures set is part of the Nuka Worlds wave for Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;Yup, it&rsquo;s a lovely bit of Power Armor, but no-one&rsquo;s bored enough to slog all over the park for those cores I&rsquo;m telling ya.&rsquo;
Many thought that the T-45 was to be the height of Power Armor technology, boy were they wrong. In an arms race that surprised exactly no one, numerous companies threw their lot into Power Armor manufacturing, even the good old Nuka-Cola Corporation went as far as putting together a suit with help from Uncle Sam. Well you know what they say, nothing sells soft drinks like imminent warfare!

This miniatures set ties-in to the Amazon TV show and includes rules for use with Fallout: Wasteland Warfare!

&lsquo;War&hellip; War Never Changes.&rsquo;
It doesn&rsquo;t matter where you go in the Wasteland, even in the most remote places people of repute can be found carving out their stories amidst the most dire of circumstances. Be they an innocent Vault-Dweller, ruthless Bounty Hunter, loyal Brotherhood soldier, or even just a good dog - there are always stories to be found in the Wasteland.

This miniatures set is part of The Wilds of Appalachia wave for Fallout: Miniatures.

&lsquo;If you ever get down to Camden Park, you&rsquo;ll probably meet Mr. Fuzzy. Not a clue who&rsquo;s inside that freaky-ass suit, but can&rsquo;t help but find their enthusiasm infectious.&rsquo;

Mr. Fuzzy is more than a mascot. Mr. Fuzzy is an ideal. A transcendental being that exists only to bring joy and cat puns to this world. So, surely, it must be the darkest of days, because Mr. Fuzzy has abandoned us, leaving only a representative in his stead. At least, that&rsquo;s how the woman currently wearing his ceremonial outfit sees it. Best leave her to it, it&rsquo;s nice to have at least one point of consistent joy in this wild Wasteland.

This miniatures set is part of The Wilds of Appalachia wave for Fallout: Miniatures.

&lsquo;It&rsquo;s weird seeing them out in the streets, Ferals still wearing whatever rags they had before everything went to shit. Makes you remember that they were people once, something more than the crazed things they are now.&rsquo;

Before the bombs dropped, most people were simply doing their best to ignore the impending doom brought on by the war. They dressed in the trappings of a normal life, their sunday best, work uniform, whatever kept the days rolling by. When a wave of nuclear radiation washed by, and their minds began to vanish as quickly as the world around them - the only scraps of their identities left were the clothes on their backs. Everything else is a faded memory, hidden behind an unquenchable, unknowable rage.

This miniatures set is part of The Wilds of Appalachia wave for Fallout: Miniatures.

&ldquo;Red eyes, glowing deep in the forests. I can see them watching me, always watching me. But when I try to find them all I find is emptiness, and a distant noise - a buzzing that burrows into my mind.&rdquo;

The Mothman has seemingly endured since long before the great war, a creature that moves through the wilds of Appalachia upon buzzing wings. Whereas cults have followed in its wake, the Mothman is not a singular creature, instead there are many of its kind across the wilds - each varied and unique in its own actions and personalities. What they want is a mystery to most - though Priests and Cultists gather in ritual to try and divine deific action from their passing. Each Mothman is an unknown, a creature that persists through all things.

This miniatures set is part of The Wilds of Appalachia wave for Fallout: Miniatures.

&ldquo;See, as best as I can tell there&rsquo;s two flavours of those crazy Moth cultists, Red and Purple. Purple keep to themselves, nice and simple. Red though, well, keep your distance, that&rsquo;s the best advice I can give.&rdquo;

Despite the name, the Cult of the Mothman is actually broken into two sects - the Enlightened, and the Followers of the Winged One. Whilst the Enlightened are generally peaceful, the Followers hold nothing but animosity towards those outside of their order - seeing outsiders as invaders of their sacred lands, as vermin. And what does one do when vermin have infested their home? You exterminate them.

This miniatures set is part of The Wilds of Appalachia wave for Fallout: Miniatures.

&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve seen them out there, bedecked in wooden totems, flailing in maddened worship around effigies and fire. There&rsquo;s so many of them these days, we can only pray they ain&rsquo;t setting up for another crusade&hellip;.&rdquo;

Gathering in places of prayer, arrayed about totems of red-eyed moths, the Cult of the Mothman can be found across Appalachia, dedicating their beings to the deific namesakes of their worship. Fanatical in their belief, the Cult bears arms against those they deem as apostates, unworthy of their lives due to their heresy against the Winged Ones. With Priests and Prophets at their head, the Cult's numbers are almost as indefatigable as their zeal.

FL1P0 is a really fast numbers game of tile flip & placement. The goal is simple: sum 10 before any of our opponents does.&nbsp;

This family friendly game offers quick games of 5-15 minutes that will leave the losers crying for an extra round, assuring a good 3-5 games per session each time it comes out on the table. It is a mix of pure luck, memory, and pattern recognition, aided by actions that will surely bring in quite funny moments for the whole family.

&mdash;description from the publisher
